"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Neha";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2685:"<p>SlideDeck is <a href="http://www.slidedeck.com/blog/news-updates/slidedeck-3-now-integrates-with-woocommerce-products/" target="_blank">integrated with WooCommerce</a>. You can create a slider to showcase your products alongwith the specifications. Here&#8217;s how &#8211;</p>\n<p><strong>STEP ONE</strong> : Choose WooCommerce in the Dynamic Sources</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/choosewoocommerce.png"><img class="size-large wp-image-17112 aligncenter" src="http://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/choosewoocommerce-580x481.png" alt="Choose WooCommerce" width="580" height="481" /></a></p>\n<p><strong>STEP TWO : </strong>Configure your WooCommerce product menu</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/configurewoocommerce.png"><img class="size-full wp-image-17113 aligncenter" src="http://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/configurewoocommerce.png" alt="configurewoocommerce" width="449" height="555" /></a></p>\n<p>And its done. You have an awesome product slider at the front-end.</p>\n<div class="slidedeck-link"><a href="http://www.slidedeck.com/blog/how-to-create-a-slider-linked-to-your-woocommerce-products/#SlideDeck-17115">My SlideDeck <small>[see the SlideDeck]</small></a></div>\n<br/><br/><a href="http://www.slidedeck.com/pricing/?utm_source=feed_ad&utm_medium=banner&utm_campaign=sd_blog"><img src="//s3.amazonaws.com/assets-slidedeck2/wp-content/themes/slidedeck2/images/sd-rss.jpg" alt="Easily create AWESOME WordPress sliders - Get SlideDeck" style="display:block;border:none;"/></a><div class="feedfla